  <thing id="rauYamTent" name="Tentacle Transformation" description="At the start of every odd-numbered round, three of Yamasoth&apos;s tentacle tips transform into one of three different types of appendages-a serpent&apos;s head, a clawed hand, or a metallic blade. The three tentacles all change into the same type of attack, and the change persists for 1 full round, after which the three tentacles revert to normal tentacles on every even-numbered round. While transformed, the limbs make the following types of attacks instead of tentacle attacks.\n\n{i}Blade:{/i} talon +36 (3d6+13/19-20)\n\n{i}Clawed Hand:{/i} claw +36 (2d6+13 plus bleed damage equal to the damage dealt by the claw)\n\n{i}Serpent Head:{/i} bite +36 (1d8+13 plus poison: bite-injury; save Fort DC 37; frequency 1/round for 12 rounds; effect 1d4 Dex drain and slowed for 1 round; cure 3 consecutive saves)" compset="RaceSpec">
